People who've experienced his faithfulness.

18:13.329 --> 18:16.793
People who've found that identity, that sense of belonging, that sense of purpose.

18:17.734 --> 18:23.741
And as I said even earlier, as you hear these stories, I just want you to think about what this looks like or could look like in your own life.

18:24.561 --> 18:28.786
But let's hear from these amazing people who can truly say the Lord has rewarded me.

18:32.066 --> 18:36.191
Hello, my name is George, this is my wife Vanessa, and we are the Liao family.

18:37.193 --> 18:45.524
When God brought us together 20 years ago, we were in a similar place spiritually, distant from God, but knowing we didn't want to stay that way.

18:46.405 --> 18:47.907
We started attending Calvary together.

18:48.528 --> 18:49.429
We couldn't get enough.

18:50.009 --> 18:55.517
We didn't want to miss one church service because every time we came, there was a major life lesson to learn.

18:56.538 --> 18:59.602
We attended just about every class that Calvary offered.

19:00.034 --> 19:04.440
At the same time, we began Bible studies with our close friends, the finds, at their home.

19:06.083 --> 19:11.030
It was what our thirsty hearts were longing for, the truth of God's word to light our path.

19:12.052 --> 19:15.196
It revealed sin in our lives that we needed to address.

19:16.298 --> 19:22.447
And with every step of obedience, we felt the blessing and favor of God coming like a gentle wind guiding us forward.

19:23.128 --> 19:27.474
We made a commitment to follow Christ and His word wholeheartedly.

19:28.258 --> 19:30.542
It was undoubtedly a turning point in our lives.

19:31.764 --> 19:36.392
We began serving together in Calvary Kids, and shortly after, we got married.

19:36.853 --> 19:43.584
We prayed, forgot to surround us with mature couples to learn from, and the Lord surely answered that prayer.

19:44.385 --> 19:49.294
When we were invited to a married couple study, the very next week we were the only newly ones there.

19:49.854 --> 19:54.322
We continued to marriage studies with these seasoned godly couples for the next few years.

19:59.010 --> 20:10.963
We greatly desire to start a family, and after a heartbreaking miscarriage, the Lord blessed us with Samuel, whose name means ask the God, exactly one year and three days after losing our first child.

20:11.944 --> 20:16.589
Our blessings tripled as a Zabella Lucas and Rebecca were given to us by our gracious God.

20:17.409 --> 20:21.053
We first learned about homeschooling from other families here at Calvary.

20:21.754 --> 20:25.618
After much prayer and surrender, we clearly saw this was the Lord's will for us.

20:25.858 --> 20:37.353
We're now in our 11th year of homeschooling, and we continue to be in awe of the faithfulness of our God in providing the finances, resources, support, and most of all the grace to respond to this calling in our lives.

20:38.094 --> 20:41.259
Our children have grown up here at Calvary serving alongside us.

20:41.859 --> 20:44.283
Today, George is an elder serving with the host team.

20:44.863 --> 20:48.008
I'm in my 18th year serving in Calvary Kids.

20:48.028 --> 20:55.698
Samuel and Lucas serve with God's guys, Isabella serves with the three-year-olds in Calvary Kids, and our Rebecca serves in Wiggles and Worship.

20:56.226 --> 21:00.352
We attend service as a family on Saturday nights and we serve together on Sundays.

21:00.913 --> 21:05.620
We love our church and the beautiful community has given to us to share in life with.

21:06.041 --> 21:09.406
We can testify that God has truly been faithful to us.

21:16.337 --> 21:17.278
Good morning, y'all.

21:17.719 --> 21:18.500
It's kind of early.

21:19.442 --> 21:20.143
My name is Victor.

21:20.764 --> 21:24.850
I'm a CCA alum and cover youth alum and today I get the blessing of serving with the youth

21:25.250 --> 21:28.193
and young adult ministry here at COVID-4 Lauderdale.

21:28.213 --> 21:30.396
One thing about me, I used to be that problem kid.

21:31.076 --> 21:34.280
Every week, my mission was to disrupt service and cause trouble in groups.

21:34.880 --> 21:35.461
That was me.

21:36.122 --> 21:41.027
But a 19 God used faithful friends led by Christ to push me to take my faith seriously.

21:41.728 --> 21:43.289
That's when everything changed.

21:43.309 --> 21:45.191
God ignited a fire in my soul.

21:45.712 --> 21:52.119
For two years, I grew in His Word, and I was hungry for truth, listening to the same teachers you all sit under right now.

21:52.980 --> 21:54.962
I loved worshiping, I loved learning.

21:55.202 --> 21:58.125
but I was still wasn't doing anything to move God's kingdom forward.

21:58.846 --> 22:00.548
That's when I finally got plugged in to serve.

22:01.169 --> 22:03.412
God wanted to use the gifts He gave me for His glory.

22:03.952 --> 22:09.399
He restored my relationship with my old youth pastor and surrounded me with brothers in Christ who now walk with me daily.

22:10.220 --> 22:14.625
Now I lead a seventh grade small group and trust me, I see glimpses of my old self in some of those guys.

22:15.306 --> 22:20.252
But just like others once pushed me closer to Jesus, now I get to pour into them and push them forward.

22:21.333 --> 22:22.194
Here's what I've learned.

22:22.754 --> 22:28.600
If I hadn't taken that step of action for Jesus, I wouldn't have the brothers, mentors, or purpose I have today.

22:29.301 --> 22:32.985
Before Christ, I didn't care about school, family, or even friendships.

22:33.606 --> 22:38.231
I was fine wasting my days away, but God had a purpose, and He revealed it through people.

22:38.732 --> 22:44.598
If it weren't for those who heard God's call and actually acted on it, my family and I wouldn't know true life in Christ.

22:45.339 --> 22:51.826
Friends became family, showing me Christlike love by sacrificing time, energy, and resources to point me towards Him.

22:52.418 --> 22:55.101
From then on, Jesus wasn't a subject in a curriculum anymore.

22:55.481 --> 22:59.285
He became someone I wanted to lean on and follow towards the abundant life he offers.

23:00.026 --> 23:04.450
That spark led me to serve, sitting in a seat and attending a group wasn't enough anymore.

23:05.211 --> 23:12.498
God put it on my heart to pour into the next generation, and I can honestly say, joining the youth in Young adult ministry here has been pure joy.

23:13.419 --> 23:20.626
My story is just one of many in this church, but if you hear anything from me today, hear this, Christ took my empty life and filled it with his joy.

23:21.090 --> 23:22.993
I can testify that God has been faithful to me.

23:31.684 --> 23:33.767
I don't know why you called me your old youth pastor.

23:33.807 --> 23:39.014
I'm pretty young, I like to think, but I can testify that he's not lying.

23:39.054 --> 23:47.986
He was a crazy middle schooler, but I never would have thought that he'd be standing on stage next to me at a service here, sharing about how God's been faithful to him.

23:48.194 --> 23:50.397
But that's how the Lord rewards us.

23:50.738 --> 23:51.760
He is the same God.

23:51.800 --> 23:52.220
Amen.

23:52.761 --> 23:53.242
Amen.

23:56.607 --> 24:02.596
Verse 33, it says, it is God who arms me with strength and keeps my way secure.

24:02.636 --> 24:07.904
He makes my feet like the feet of a deer, and he causes me to stand on the heights.

24:08.846 --> 24:10.869
He trains my hands for battle.

24:11.650 --> 24:13.613
My arms can bend a bow of bronze.

24:14.354 --> 24:16.658
You make your saving help, my shield,

24:17.058 --> 24:18.400
Your help has made me great.

24:19.201 --> 24:24.227
You provide a broad path for my feet so that my ankles do not give way.

24:24.447 --> 24:27.350
Number three, if you're taking notes, love what David says here.

24:27.370 --> 24:30.734
He says, he trains my hands for battle.

24:31.475 --> 24:33.297
He trains my hands for battle.

24:33.578 --> 24:35.881
How many of you know that we're in the middle of a war?

24:35.901 --> 24:38.023
A spiritual war.

24:38.043 --> 24:43.730
A war for the souls of a nation, of the world.

24:43.810 --> 24:45.793
of our youth, of everyone.

24:45.813 --> 24:47.996
There's a very real war happening.

24:48.977 --> 25:06.500
And we all, I used to sing it all the time as a little kid, I may never march in the infantry, anyone, ride in the chute, I may never, because I'm in the Lord's army.

25:06.540 --> 25:08.043
I need everyone to salute, ready?

25:08.523 --> 25:10.426
I'm in the Lord's army.

25:11.707 --> 25:12.388
All right, I like that.

25:12.488 --> 25:13.650
Cool, that was awesome.

25:14.562 --> 25:17.467
David says he trains my hands for battle.

25:19.129 --> 25:19.790
We're in a battle.

25:21.152 --> 25:24.918
But the beautiful part of it is we're in a battle of a war that's already been won.

25:26.000 --> 25:31.568
It's over, it's finished, it's done, the end is written, we see it, spoiler alert, read the end of the book.

25:32.850 --> 25:33.672
Jesus is already won.

25:34.393 --> 25:35.735
We get to fight a winning fight.

25:36.556 --> 25:38.159
We get to fight a fight with confidence.

25:39.240 --> 25:42.866
But what I love is he doesn't just take us and go, go fight, good luck.

25:43.554 --> 25:44.515
But it says he trains us.

25:46.117 --> 25:51.024
I love, there's nothing I love more in a movie than a training montage, right?

25:51.044 --> 25:52.566
I think of the Rocky movies.

25:56.230 --> 25:58.353
He's like punching the meat, you know what I'm talking about?

25:58.373 --> 26:00.215
Anyone, Drogo!

26:00.816 --> 26:06.143
Anytime I'm standing on, it doesn't matter if it's like a five foot hill or like Pike's Peak in Colorado.

26:06.163 --> 26:07.465
I'm Drogo!

26:08.005 --> 26:11.570
There's nothing, a training montage pumps you up.

26:12.098 --> 26:15.825
Like you watch a training montage in a movie and you get so excited.

26:15.865 --> 26:28.828
To me, those parts of a movie where the main character is getting prepared for the end of the movie, the big climatic moment, the big fight scene, the big battle, whatever it is, like the training scene is more exciting to me than the actual battle.

26:29.649 --> 26:30.991
I don't know why it just is.

26:31.192 --> 26:32.434
It gets me fired up.

26:32.706 --> 26:39.796
So like when Rocky comes on and those scenes, it's like, I want to start doing push-ups in my house and squats and I try to come up with these unconventional methods.

26:40.096 --> 26:41.818
I don't know if punching meets a good idea.

26:41.878 --> 26:47.786
My wife got mad because I had a chicken tender out and I was like doing this and she's like, Sean, I don't think that's how it works.

26:49.369 --> 26:49.809
I don't know.

26:50.831 --> 26:53.654
Maybe you haven't seen Rocky, maybe you're a Mulan fan.

26:53.714 --> 26:55.437
Let's get down to business.

26:56.078 --> 26:59.282
It doesn't matter what training scene, but I want you to picture that.

27:00.738 --> 27:05.744
We might not fight battles like David did, but as I said, we're still in a battle.

27:07.666 --> 27:09.228
We're in a battle for souls.

27:10.870 --> 27:15.415
We're in a battle where I feel like the world is trying more and more and more to pull people away from Jesus.

27:17.497 --> 27:19.860
Yet we're fighting for their eternity.

27:21.542 --> 27:23.504
We're fighting for their hearts, for their souls.

27:25.546 --> 27:28.690
It might look different today, but we're still fighting.

27:29.506 --> 27:32.771
So we have a couple more testimonies that we're gonna hear here in a second.

27:34.313 --> 27:37.218
And these aren't from actual soldiers.

27:38.720 --> 27:58.130
They're not from amazing, like the most talented, and Tyreek and Jamie, please don't take offense to this, but the stories we're gonna hear from them is not people who are the most talented people in the world, and they're so amazing, and they just got this awesome gift, and that's why they're able to pour in and fight for the next generation.

27:59.298 --> 28:04.706
But what you're gonna hear in these stories is people who very simply said, God, use me.

28:06.849 --> 28:09.092
As I promise you, if your prayer is God, use me.

28:10.114 --> 28:11.996
Heal, equip, empower you to be used.

28:13.158 --> 28:14.800
He calls us his hands and feet.

28:16.022 --> 28:17.484
He wants to use you.

28:18.826 --> 28:20.268
And you don't do it on your own.

28:20.328 --> 28:24.955
David said, he equips my, he trains my hands for battle.

28:25.476 --> 28:27.058
God's the one who equips us.

28:27.234 --> 28:28.696
God's the one who empowers us.

28:28.736 --> 28:32.080
He just wants willing vessels who will say, use me.

28:33.321 --> 28:38.968
So as you listen to their stories, I want you to have that same thought, is how is the Lord trying to train me?

28:39.809 --> 28:42.151
How does the Lord want to use me to fight his battles?

28:43.273 --> 28:45.715
How does the Lord want to use my life for his glory?

28:46.657 --> 28:50.881
But let's hear these stories of people who can truly say he trains my hands for battle.

28:52.543 --> 28:53.044
Hello, everyone.

28:53.605 --> 28:54.866
My name is Tyrek Smith.

28:55.330 --> 29:08.249
I've been serving in the family ministry as the leader for the past 13 years to whom I lovingly refer to as my God's guys, a group of around 20 middle and high school boys that help around with the teachers and parents however we can.

29:09.211 --> 29:15.360
I'm sure all the men in the room can testify to how much of an adventure those years were and how much you soak up during that time as well.

29:15.941 --> 29:24.914
I think there's a healthy amount of pressure in knowing that I have so many young boys in that phase of their life looking up to me, expecting me to be a good example for them.

29:25.378 --> 29:43.476
It pushes me to be more patient, to be more stern when needed, to study the Bible more, especially the questions that kids around those ages are grappling with, knowing the truth of who God is and what His word teaches in depth is extremely important, especially with so much misunderstanding or misinterpretations in the world.

29:44.457 --> 29:49.261
As a leader, I do my best to see where my God's guys are spiritually, to talk to them, to pray for them.

29:49.742 --> 29:54.066
I also do a Bible study with them every Sunday that focuses on different aspects of our faith.

29:54.530 --> 30:00.779
We're going through the book of Mark right now because I felt called to ensure that my newer, younger guys had a solid understanding of the gospel.

30:01.420 --> 30:18.544
My main focus, generally, is on how to study the Bible, implement it, and teach it to others, which is inspired by 1 Peter 3.5, which says, in your heart, honor Christ the Lord as holy, always being prepared to make a defense to anyone who asks you for a reason for the hope that is in you.

30:19.085 --> 30:22.930
And the key word to me is prepared, getting the next generation ready.

30:23.266 --> 30:28.954
I'm happy to say that two of my oldest God guys have graduated and have been serving as leaders themselves for over a year now.

30:29.394 --> 30:31.577
Caleb in the high school ministry is a small groups leader.

30:31.898 --> 30:34.601
Chris in the family ministry is a small groups leader to the third graders.

30:35.082 --> 30:39.488
And God's willing, more of my guys will continue to grow as leaders for those that come after them.

30:39.848 --> 30:42.712
And I can testify that I will keep fighting for the next generation.

30:43.093 --> 30:49.962
And I hope you will too.

30:49.982 --> 30:50.443
Good morning.

30:51.584 --> 30:52.946
My name is Jamie Stefanik.

30:53.762 --> 31:01.615
And for the last eight years, I've had the honor and the privilege to serve with our youth in high school ministry, as well as serve with the young girls in CYA.

31:02.396 --> 31:11.691
It's been such a blessing being able to lead a small group of CYA girls on my house every week with my co-leader and my best friend, Donna Green, who I would not be able to do this without.

31:12.372 --> 31:20.946
Through mentoring these young ladies, we've had the opportunity to watch God move so powerfully in their lives and see the immense blessings that God has bestowed through mentorship.

31:21.666 --> 31:29.275
When we first started this group, we lifted it up to the Lord and asked that He would allow it to be a group where these ladies could find good, solid community.

31:29.956 --> 31:31.798
Wow, were we blown away.

31:32.800 --> 31:38.447
God handpicked each of these ladies and brought several of them to our group in ways only that He could orchestrate.

31:39.308 --> 31:51.122
Some I met in the New Believer's room after they had just given their life to the Lord, others at the altar during a time of prayer, and even just for that one who was sitting by herself in the sanctuary after service,

31:51.426 --> 31:54.729
Praying for someone to come speak to her, and God led me right to her.

31:55.730 --> 32:03.958
We've watched this little community lean on each other and help each other through the ups and downs of life as they pray for one another with a true heart for each other that comes only from God.

32:05.119 --> 32:10.884
The friendships these girls have made with each other, not even knowing one another until this group started our life giving.

32:11.925 --> 32:14.948
But not just for the girls, it's also brought life back to me.

32:20.153 --> 32:21.074
Seven years ago,

32:22.466 --> 32:25.869
my 28 year old daughter Rachel went home to be with the Lord.

32:27.891 --> 32:30.534
And this sent me into a spiral of such deep grief.

32:31.435 --> 32:32.936
And I didn't think that I would ever come out of it.

32:34.658 --> 32:50.674
But God, God reached down and he tugged at my heart and he plays an intense desire to go and mentor girls so that they would know that someone cares for them deeply and they wanted to hear their issues, be there for them and lead them back to God's word.

32:51.586 --> 32:55.131
Herein lies my passion for working with these young women.

32:56.473 --> 33:04.806
I am now daily living up the verse in Joel 2.25 that says, so I will restore to you the years that the swarming locus has eaten.

33:05.607 --> 33:14.761
God has been and is still now restoring me through these beautiful girls who I have this joyous chance to speak into their lives as they speak right back into my life.

33:15.643 --> 33:20.530
I thank God for nudging me to mentor as well as the blessings that he's given me through these community of young women.

33:21.250 --> 33:28.137
When it feels like progress is slow or you don't feel like you're making a difference, trust that God is at work in the hearts of those that you're mentoring.

33:28.837 --> 33:41.570
So when you hear that small gentle voice telling you, this is the way, walk in it, do not hesitate to answer that call, but be prepared to see all that God can and he will do through your obedience to him.

33:41.610 --> 33:46.255
As you step into whatever role God is calling you to, remember that you're not doing it alone.

33:46.755 --> 33:49.618
When God calls you to something, he will not only equip you,

33:49.794 --> 33:51.756
but he will walk with you every step of the way.

33:52.437 --> 33:55.641
I can testify that I will keep fighting for the next generation.

34:03.309 --> 34:11.579
I just wanna take a second and talk to the parents in the room, but maybe even, maybe you feel a calling to be a spiritual parent to someone.

34:12.520 --> 34:18.066
Maybe you're in the room and you're only like seven or 15, but listen to this because one day you will be a parent.

34:18.402 --> 34:22.528
And one day the Lord is going to use you in an incredible way in your own kids' lives.

34:23.569 --> 34:35.185
I love hearing these stories, these testimonies of people who've stepped up, who work full time, who come and volunteer on the weekends and say, I want the Lord to use me to invest in someone else.

34:36.507 --> 34:38.470
But the truth is, it starts at home.

34:39.932 --> 34:44.398
Our investment in our kids is the most important thing that we could ever do.

34:44.478 --> 34:47.602
It's the most important calling God has on the life of a parent.

34:49.442 --> 34:55.170
And my hope, my prayer is one day as a father of a three-year-old that my son will grow up to say these things.

34:55.250 --> 34:56.091
You have saved me.

34:56.251 --> 34:57.393
The Lord has rewarded me.

34:57.433 --> 34:58.855
He trains my hands for battle.

35:00.697 --> 35:01.719
But that starts now.

35:03.281 --> 35:04.803
That starts with pouring into him now.

35:04.863 --> 35:06.505
That starts with investing in him now.

35:07.246 --> 35:16.018
I want to show you a slide that I think an incredible way shows us the impact that we as parents can have on our children.

35:17.282 --> 35:20.165
And it's this, it's from our friends at this organization called One Hope.

35:20.185 --> 35:28.633
They do a lot of surveys and research and stuff like this, but they basically asked 11 to 13 year olds.

35:28.653 --> 35:31.176
That's Jen Alpha, anyone ever hear of Jen Alpha?

35:31.356 --> 35:39.664
So like Jen Alpha, depending on what people, people have different views of their age, but some people would consider some of them freshmen already.

35:39.745 --> 35:41.366
So it's truly the next generation.

35:41.386 --> 35:45.170
They're moving on up, but they interviewed 11 to 13 year olds.

35:45.826 --> 35:51.692
And they asked this question, hey, do you read your Bible at least once a week on your own?

35:52.913 --> 36:07.968
And here's what was so fascinating that this survey showed us is that 67% of those who said, I read the Bible on my own at least once a week said their parent also reads the Bible with them.

36:09.130 --> 36:09.910
So think about that.

36:10.991 --> 36:13.554
If you read your Bible with your kid,

36:14.146 --> 36:16.750
They are more likely to read it on their own.

36:17.971 --> 36:24.560
Compared to those who said, my parents don't read it with me, only 10% said they read their Bible on their own.

36:25.341 --> 36:27.825
And you can look at those other stats right down there too.

36:28.366 --> 36:32.652
And it says, hey, 58% just said, their parents don't even read the Bible with them.

36:33.513 --> 36:36.236
They just see their parent reading the Bible.

36:36.297 --> 36:43.186
I don't think you realize the impact of just having this open on the table and your kids seeing you read it has.

36:43.810 --> 36:50.982
58 percent that read the Bible on their own once a week at least said their parent.

36:51.002 --> 36:56.211
They see their parent read the Bible compared to only 14 percent who said they don't.

36:57.032 --> 37:07.890
And what one hope found was this wasn't just true when it came to reading the Bible, but it was the same pattern that they saw when it came to prayer and sharing their faith with others.

37:08.834 --> 37:30.784
And I was in Pasadena this past week at this place called Fuller Youth Institute, who also does a lot of research, and something I left with after they interviewed 3,000 people between the ages of 13 and 17, 1,000 of them weren't even Christians, is young people across the board find their identity, their belonging, and their purpose starting at home.

37:32.045 --> 37:38.514
Young people are more likely to go to home and their parents than they are to go to their youth pastor or small group leader, believe it or not.

37:39.202 --> 37:43.409
They're more likely to turn to their home to find their sense of identity before they would come to church.

37:44.090 --> 37:48.336
They feel like they most belong at home than they do at school, than they do online.

37:48.557 --> 37:50.800
The online numbers were actually really low.

37:50.860 --> 37:51.782
It was shocking to me.

37:52.803 --> 37:57.811
But the home is like rising up in an incredible way, and we have an amazing opportunity.

37:59.113 --> 38:02.659
And I know some of you might be sitting in your seat and be like, my kid's 17, I mess.

38:02.779 --> 38:04.722
It's never too late to start.

38:05.218 --> 38:06.600
We talked about Rocky earlier.

38:06.620 --> 38:09.964
If you remember in Rocky 6, he's like 80 years old and he's still fighting.

38:10.004 --> 38:13.608
It's never too late to start.

38:14.470 --> 38:15.831
You might not know where to start though.

38:16.652 --> 38:19.055
We mentioned our QR code earlier on the back of the seats.

38:19.075 --> 38:19.776
You can scan that.

38:19.796 --> 38:27.666
We actually have a parenting talk on Thursday this week, all about technology, how to talk to your kids about, how to deal with all the crazy stuff in technology.

38:28.908 --> 38:34.034
But we also have other resources, like literally just, here's questions to ask your kid after you read the Bible together.

38:34.274 --> 38:35.676
Here's a Bible reading plan.

38:36.457 --> 38:42.064
In the same way he trains our hands for battle, we want to equip you and empower you to be the primary discipler in your home.

38:42.805 --> 38:44.006
So scan that QR code.

38:44.026 --> 38:45.668
There's so many resources for you.

38:46.229 --> 38:48.772
